






THE ARMADA — Armada Brewing























































THE ARMADA







Cursed King IPA 6.5% ABV 66 IBUsOur leading American IPA is loaded with hoppy goodness and has a crisp malt finish. Time to step your hop game up and endulge. 







Fortune Raider Double IPA 8% 95 IBUsDo you like hops? Well you're sure to get your dose of some hoppy love here. Dry hopped twice to rock your fucking senses with citrus, stone fruit, and berries. 







White Storm Pale Ale 6.2% 50 IBU'sWe throw in a hefty amount of wheat malt to give you a soft mouthfeel and compliment the heavy doses of hops in here. Hazy by malt not yeast. 







Death of Corruption Black IPA 7.5% 90 IBUsThis killer right here is everything you ever wanted in a Black IPA. Light roasted character that doesn't interfere with the hop bitterness, delicate malt sweetness and loaded with a boatload of American hops in the whirlpool and dry hopped to whack you over the head with hoppy deliciousness.







Coffee King IPA 6.5% 66 IBUs Draft OnlyOur Cursed King made a deal with the devil to give you the best of both worlds. Hops and Coffee! If you were looking for a morning beer. You just found it. 







Savage Queen Double IPA 8% 85 IBUThe Queens beauty is expressed through a delicate malt profile and a load of tropical fruit, citrus, and berry. Brewed with Rakau, Mosaic and El Dorado hops.







Ghost of Atlantis Dry-Hopped Farmhouse Ale 6% 30 IBUA delicate and crisp malt backed with a tart and spicy finish from our Farmhouse yeast makes this brew super sessionable. We then dry-hop this beer with Huell Melon and Mandarina Bavaria hop to compliment the wonderful yeast.







Liberty Abandoned Russian Imperial Stout 9.5% 75 IBUsThis imperial stout is rich in malt flavor with chocolate, caramel, berry, and hints of burnt marshmallow leading the show. We use a load of English hops in the boil to give this puppy a firm bitterness to stand up to the large amounts of malt we use to get the alcohol level up.  Drink Fresh!Our beers are brewed in small batches, we use a lot of hops and we do not filter our beer. For your experience to be as amazing as we anticipated, we suggest consuming our beers within 1-2 months from packaging, though our beer is good to last up to 6 months. (see below for dates) Since our beers are not filtered some yeast is still in suspension of the beer when packaged. Though we do our best to minimize this with a thorough cold condition period, you may see that some sediment has formed on the bottom of the bottle. This is completely natural. We recommend storing Armada beers upright and in a fridge at least 1 hour prior to consumption. Enjoy!You say 750's are dead? We are here to resurrect them!ARMADA's mission is to bring together community around great beer. Just like a bottle of wine, 750's are the perfect size for sharing with friends. Break it into multiple glasses and toast to friends and good health. Quit it with the single serving sized beers and get down to sharing. This is your Captain speaking.Recycle please. Take care of OUR planet. Homebrewers reuse our bottles! We specifically chose a manufacturer of ARMADA labels that offered a product that stuck well, but was also easily removable. Crazy huh? No more scrapping, just peel, clean, sanitize and fill!Packaging DatesBatch #1 Cursed King IPA Bottled on 1/14/17Batch #2 Fortune Raider Double IPA Bottled on 2/26/17Batch #3 White Storm Pale Ale Bottled on 4/8/17Batch #4 Death of Corruption Black IPA 4/23/17Batch #5 Cursed King IPA TBD 








